<p>Genitopatellar syndrome is a rare disorder consisting of microcephaly, severe psychomotor retardation, and characteristic coarse facial features, including broad nose and small or retracted chin, associated with congenital flexion contractures of the lower extremities, abnormal or missing patellae, and urogenital anomalies (summary by Penttinen et al., 2009).</p>

<p>[Penttinen, M., Koillinen, H., Niinikoski, H., Makitie, O., Hietala, M. Genitopatellar syndrome in an adolescent female with severe osteoporosis and endocrine abnormalities. Am. J. Med. Genet. 149A: 451-455, 2009.]<br/></p>